The Federal Capital Territory Administration (FCTA) has reiterated its determination to complete or recycle all abandoned projects in the area councils of the Federal Capital Territory (FCT) for the benefit of the communities. Speaking during an interview with newsmen on plans and target to improve the welfare of residents of communities in the six area councils of the FCT, acting secretary, Area Councils Services Secretariat (ACSS), Mrs. Omolola Olanipekun, revealed that the secretariat, in collaboration with the Health Secretariat, would conduct a survey to ascertain the health needs of communities. Olanipekun added that the ACSS would also introduce some nongovernmental organisations (NGOs) to communities, so that residents of the communities can benefit from the empowerment programmes of the organisations. She added that the secretariat would also focus on the provision of water, environmental sanitation, health, security, education, staff welfare and a lot of other things, in the New Year, adding that secretariat would align with other the secretariats to the development of the area councils.  